Suspension of All India service officers will be in rare of rare cases and in those circumstances where the said officers commit an offence (civil or criminal) and there is substantial evidence to bring him/her to answer before a adminstrative committee chair by chief secretary. Even after all of this drama, if he or she found guilty the state via chief minister's office require to send approval from centre i.e DoPT within 48 hours. Moreover the officer can later approach high court against the order...the article 311 explicitly describe provisions of removal, dismissal and transfer of central adminstrative officer...So In a nutshell I would say Suspension is very easy to say but lets be real it is not that easy to execute it is far more easy to simply transfer him in order to avoid unnecessary complex proceedings. Several times supreme court had reminded that All India services members belongs to centre, they are being simply lend to states for administrative position unlike state cadres they have certain immunity regarding suspension, transfer, remuneration of perks etc....

@Kamei JohnWilson sir, you are definitely not wrong. I completely understand the necessity of having a larger agglomeration like pan naga in Manipur context. Its uniquely diverse. Iam simply trying to understand the Nation definition criteria here. When we say KuKi-Chin-Mizo its just like Ze-Liang- Rong.   Zemei- Liangmei- Rongmei all distributed in Manipur, Assam, Nagaland, etc. Diverse but same root of a large tree in terms of language and intrinsic culture. Just that the size is bigger in case of KuKi-Chin-Mizo. Same thing for the Meitei Salai7. Same thing for Britain/UK - Scottish, Irish, english. Same for Israel-12tribes/sons but all speak Hebrew/Aramaic bonded by1 Abraham and holy book Torah. Maybe slightly different cultures, different accents but 1 rooted nation and language. We can't ignore the Language criteria at all when we try to define a nation. At least till the present era. Ukhrul and Mao are just neighbors for generations but they are very uniquely different in language and culture . Eg: the manipur naga festival Lui-Ngai-Ni: lui- tangkhul, Ngai-rongmei, Ni- mao. The words might make sense when seperated but when you combine its very confusing and unoriginal. What about anal, lamkang, monsang, thangal, etc in this? The spirit of uniting tribes can be apllauded but the tribe historical fabrication and alterations just to reach the top of power hierarchy or eliminate another tribe like Kuki by Ukhrul is unfortunate. And yes I am always open to learning if I am factually wrong sir.

If the state cabinet decided not to introduce the Bill or reject on the HAC recommendation Bill or any contention lies thereof, The recommendation shall then be forwarded to Governor for his discretion, this is allowed in 3rd schedule matters 12A. Manipur Legislative Assembly (HAC) order 1972. This means that even if HAC recommendation is rejected by Cabinet before tabling in the house still Governor has the discretion to take a call.

Parallel administration is already enshrined under the provision Article 371C. The ADC amendment Bill 2021 is constitutionally valid. If Manipur consider itself as a state under india union. Then it should abide by constitutional process. The Bill should be introduced in the ongoing assembly session, so that all the good, bad, and ugly needs to be discussed and debated. Whether to pass the Bill or not lies with the elected representatives. Democratic values and constitutional process should not be suppressed. As per Constitution, the recommendation Bill should be forwarded to Governor for his discretion(3rd schedule 12A, HAC order 1972) if state cabinet decided not to introduce the Bill in the assembly.

Blinded by false pride, the majority community refuses to acknowledge the existence of Article 371(C) of our Constitution for the last several decades. Manipur Land Revenue and Land Reforms Act 1960, coupled with Hill Area Committee divided the hill and valley people drawing a clear line of demarcation in all respects. Even the Yelhoumee (original inhabitants) status is divided. While the one is officially recognised, the other is unofficial and looks like self styled Yelhoumee. We should call a spade a spade. Article 342(1) made all this division and unless the social disparity among the original inhabitants is removed by a Constitutional amendment -- either majority community becoming ST or ST friends general -- the status quo will remain always, with Meitei at the receiving end forever. At this rate, the geopolitical reality demands a collective political wisdom devoid of quixotic pipe dreams.

But the point is if the Nagas want administrative or political unification, don't thr Nagas have the right to do so when the Art.3 of the Indian Constitution allows the Parliament to change any State's boundary if required which indicates the supremacy of National Integration over any State's Integration resolution/s, which is why Jharkhand from Bihar,Chhatigarh from M.P., Uttarkhand from U.P., Telingana from T.N. etc have been done. If Nagas along with land chose Nagalim rather than Manipur, then the majority communities the Meiteis need to reflect of their past mistakes like superior-complex psyche ( Hau-mangye attitude), manipulative-habits ( CSS funds must be first screen by Tammis and then meagre-amount to Chingmis, exploitation of Chingmis' ST quotas in educational, employments, MLAs composition etc matters) ,etc...

Don't you have any other excuses other than " mangba sengba" which happened 50-60 years back but no longer exists today. Have you experience personally. As if you people are only oppressed. What about      (1) those Meitei officers who were slaughtered and oppressed in hilly areas      2)those drivers who are facing all sorts of attrocities caused by your leaders so called NSCN etc.etc. Even I know a truck driver from my locality who was slaughtered in hill with his private part chopped off some years back just for ransom. Have you ever heard of tribal people killed by Meitei.      3) Have you ever seen Meitei dwelling in hills, Ukhrul ,for example. But you must have seen a lot of tribal inhabited areas and 'khuns' in the heart of Imphal city as well as all over the valley. And you people are always shouting Meitei are trying to snatch your land. Yes Meitei's share is for all but your share is exclusively yours.      4)At least you people are secured with ST quota for almost everything, from education to job. Where is Meitei's except for some belonging to SC? I myself grew up as an orphan in an economically very unstable family in somewhat remote village. And I saw a lot of my rich tribal friend got selected in entrance exam without much effort just because they belong to tribal community. But for me no such benefit.Why? Bcoz I belong to Meitei community. The only means was to work harder than them.      5) You are shouting Why less number of representatives from hills when majority of population are dwelling in valley including your tribal people. Constituencies are made on the basis of number of population. More population means more representatives.      Don't you have your local representatives ,MLAs ,ministers. Where have hill area development committee gone? Where have the funds gone? Your leaders are residing may be in Imphal or in Delhi in multi storey apartment with luxury lifestyle.      NOT ALL TRIBAL ARE UNDERPRIVILEGED. NOT ALL MEITEI'S ARE PRIVILEGED. AFTER ALL ALL THE POORS SUFFER AND ALL THE RICH ENJOY THEIR LIFE IRRESPECTIVE OF COMMUNITY.ITS HAVE VS HAVENOTS NOT MEITEI VS TRIBAL.      Yes I agree that our leaders are bad including your hill representatives. We have to raise voice against them.      WE ALL INCLUDING YOU NEED TO SEE THE MATTERS FROM OTHERS PERSPECTIVE ALSO NOT JUST FROM YOUR PREOCCUPIED ONE ONLY. HOPE YOU UNDERSTAND.

The rules and regulations of a society are designed by their most intellectual and well experienced individuals. But if the next generation find it offensive/unsuitable w.r.t. their lifestyle than they can modify the same for the betterment of the whole. People make the rules and with time peoples changes and their mindset change and hence the rules are bound to change. When a society is against the changing human trend then they will be left behind. This is the reason why the most religious fanatic societies/countries are the most underdeveloped/backward one. The Caste Disabilities Removal Act, 1850 ( The Freedom of Religion Act). - A person renouncing his religion or losing his caste is not deprived of his rights of inheritance under the Act.   2\. The Hindu Widows' Remarriage Act, 1856-The Act legalized remarriage of Hindu widows in certain cases and declared their rights and disabilities on remarriage.   3\. The Child Marriage Restrain Act, 1929 (Sharda Act).- The Act related to the restraints on the solemnisation of child marriages.   4\. The Guardians and Wards Act, 1890.- It applied to appointment of guardians by the Court.   So far many personal law has been reforming and supersedes for the betterment of the India.. As of now in Hindu law there are 26 ( twenty six) different Acts which have been passed.

I would like to make a point regarding the genesis of the word "Pangal". This is my opinion based on facts, common sense and logic. Bengalis (irrespective of religion) are basically divided into two "groups" ie: Bengalis from West Bengal and those from present day Bangladesh. The WB Bengalis are called "ghotis" while that from Bangladesh are called "bongals". This grouping is purely based on their geographical location. When the Bongal Muslims (mostly from Sylhet) came to Manipur in the 1500s and 1600s, they were called as Pangals as the Meiteis could not pronounce the word "bongals" properly. And this became the byword as the word "pangal"/strength is in the Meitei lexicon. By this reasoning, Shanti Das Gosain (who was from Sylhet and a Hindu) is also a Pangal/Bongal who came in 1700s.

This is how history is manipulated and used by your masters when you don't guard your own.   History has always been monopolised by those agencies in power. It has been dictated and made to be accepted. When knowledge is subjected to such monopoly, it doesnt stay away from the power politics of distorting history for their own benefits and convenience. When your time dimension is let to be manipulated,distorted and misinterpreted, the space you exist will be distorted.
